    <briefdescription>
<para>Power Manager class for AXO X1 devices derived from Power Manager base class. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Detailed Description </title><para>The power manager X1 class provides the following timer:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>BoostCtrlTimer: <ref refid="class_timer" kindref="compound">Timer</ref> to control boost on before initial metrics tx (eLteWakeTmo)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>myTLteStartDelayTimerimer3: <ref refid="class_timer" kindref="compound">Timer</ref> to control inital LTE start delay (eLteStartTmo)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>AdxlWakeupTimer: <ref refid="class_timer" kindref="compound">Timer</ref> to control adxl wakeup to measurements tx (eLteWakeTmo) It provides a method to request switching on and off the boost converter, methods to request RMS, environment, battery, HW and LTE reports for metrics collection and methods to report reset cause and boot counter to the data manager task. It furthermore implements the from base class required methods taskInit and message_handler, which are called in the task function provided by the base class. <bold>Message Interaction:</bold></para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Receive<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Timer interrupt callback</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>LTE connector task</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>MQTT connector task</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>RMS store task</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Power manager task</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Transmit<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Boost converter task</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>RMS store task</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>SHTCX task</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Battery manager task</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>HW Metrics task</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Data manager task</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Power manager task (self, transmission in timer callback) </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
